NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT, IxNetwork-NGPF

Used to configure simulating subscriber lines behind an ANCP enabled Access Node.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle. Default: None

Valid options are:

create

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory.

modify

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is

delete

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is

enable

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and

disable

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and

enable_all

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is

disable_all

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle. Default: None Valid choices are: create - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. This mode will create a DSL Profile and DSL Resync profile and add it to the profiles used by the ANCP Client. If an identical profile already exists it will be used instead of creating a new one. modify - handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. All the TLVs will be removed from this profile and new ones will be added according to the procedure parameters. In this case the parameters will not accept lists (single values only). delete - handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. The DSL Profile specified with -handle will be removed. enable - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter. disable - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will stop using the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter. enable_all - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use all DSL Profiles available. disable_all - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will not use any DSL Profiles.

DEFAULT

 None

-profile_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter is used to specify what kind of DSL profile should be created.Default: bothDependencies: None

Valid options are:

dsl_sync

Create only a DSL sync profile.

dsl_resync

Create only a DSL resync profile.

both

Create both DSL sync and resync profiles.

DEFAULT

 None

-percentage

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Percent of subscribers that will use each profile. Valid only for -mode 'create'.May be a list, needs to have the following format: {x1 x2 x3 y1 y2 y3...} where x, y are the percentages for multiple profiles (needs to have the same length as actual_rate_upstream, for example).The number of such groups needs to be the same as the length of ancp_client_handle.

DEFAULT

'0'

A list containing the ancp subscriber lines protocol stack handles that were added by the command (if any).

$::SUCCESS | $::FAILURE, Status of procedure call.

log

When status is failure, contains more information.

handle

<ancp_subscriber_lines_handle> Please note that this key will be omitted if the current session or command were run with -return_detailed_handles 0.

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT, IxNetwork-NGPF

Used to configure simulating subscriber lines behind an ANCP enabled Access Node.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle. Default: None

Valid options are:

create

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory.

modify

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is

delete

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is

enable

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and

disable

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and

enable_all

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is

disable_all

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle. Default: None Valid choices are: create - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. This mode will create a DSL Profile and DSL Resync profile and add it to the profiles used by the ANCP Client. If an identical profile already exists it will be used instead of creating a new one. modify - handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. All the TLVs will be removed from this profile and new ones will be added according to the procedure parameters. In this case the parameters will not accept lists (single values only). delete - handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. The DSL Profile specified with -handle will be removed. enable - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter. disable - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will stop using the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter. enable_all - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use all DSL Profiles available. disable_all - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will not use any DSL Profiles.

DEFAULT

 None

profile_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter is used to specify what kind of DSL profile should be created.Default: bothDependencies: None

Valid options are:

dsl_sync

Create only a DSL sync profile.

dsl_resync

Create only a DSL resync profile.

both

Create both DSL sync and resync profiles.

 None

'0'

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT, IxNetwork-NGPF

Used to configure simulating subscriber lines behind an ANCP enabled Access Node.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle. Default: None

Valid options are:

create

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory.

modify

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is

delete

handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is

enable

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and

disable

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and

enable_all

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is

disable_all

ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Used to specify the action that the function will perform on the given ANCP Client session handle. Every mode except create, enable_all, and disable_all requires a valid AN Subscriber Line Pool handle. Modes create, enable_all, and disable_all will perform on any given ANCP Client handle. Default: None Valid choices are: create - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. This mode will create a DSL Profile and DSL Resync profile and add it to the profiles used by the ANCP Client. If an identical profile already exists it will be used instead of creating a new one. modify - handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. All the TLVs will be removed from this profile and new ones will be added according to the procedure parameters. In this case the parameters will not accept lists (single values only). delete - handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config is mandatory. The DSL Profile specified with -handle will be removed. enable - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter. disable - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config and handle returned by emulation_ancp_subscriber_lines_config are mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will stop using the DSL Profile specified with -handle parameter. enable_all - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will use all DSL Profiles available. disable_all - ancp_client_handle returned by emulation_ancp_config is mandatory. The ANCP client specified with ancp_client_handle will not use any DSL Profiles.

DEFAULT

 None

profile_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter is used to specify what kind of DSL profile should be created.Default: bothDependencies: None

Valid options are:

dsl_sync

Create only a DSL sync profile.

dsl_resync

Create only a DSL resync profile.

both

Create both DSL sync and resync profiles.

 None
